A woman who claims she was wrongfully diagnosed with HIV and placed on anti-retroviral treatment wants the hospital to admit liability.She has threatened to sue the&nbsp;Kwale health centre for &quot;medical negligence&quot; and &quot;falsification of facts&quot; if the institution fails to admit its mistake.Esther Mwakazi claims she was diagnosed with the HIV virus when she visited the hospital in Diani on July 20, this year, for ante-natal care. She alleges that medical staff told her she was carrying the virus after tests and placed her on life-prolonging medication.Esther claims she discovered the mistake three months into the ARV regime after she and her husband sought opinions from three other hospitals in Kwale and Mombasa.